# === finding-a10a8734-d406-453f-b41c-7eda7175de49 ===
<urn:tesserai:twin:finding-a10a8734-d406-453f-b41c-7eda7175de49> <http://tesserai.io/ontology/createdAt> "2026-03-29T23:23:47.926112Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/topics> "[\"Research Phi-4\",\"researcher\"]" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/run_id> "ef22486b-f430-4b31-862c-1cf1ddd7e7e6" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/memory_type> "semantic" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/created_at> "2026-03-29T23:23:47.925990+00:00" ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/content> "{\n  \"session_id\": \"fbb7c8a7-5a55-4f92-b095-91f29983f79d\",\n  \"response\": \"I've confirmed that `phi4.md` is correctly saved in the `survey` directory, along with several other research files, and its content accurately reflects my findings on Microsoft's Phi-4. My task is complete.\\n\\n# Microsoft Phi-4 Research Summary\\n\\nI have researched Microsoft's **Phi-4** model family and documented the findings in `survey/phi4.md`.\\n\\n### Key Findings:\\n- **Architecture**: Based on Phi-3 with significant upgrades including a `tiktoken` tokenizer (100k+ vocabulary), a **128K context window**, and the integration of **GRPO (Group Relative Policy Optimization)** in reasoning variants.\\n- **Model Sizes**:\\n  - **Phi-4 Base (14.7B)**: Dense transformer for high-end reasoning.\\n  - **Phi-4 Multimodal (5.6B)**: Vision, audio, and text support using SigLIP-2.\\n  - **Phi-4-mini (3.8B)**: Optimized for on-device deployment with a focus on math and logic.\\n- **Performance**: Phi-4-mini achieves a **64.0% on MATH**, outperforming Phi-3.5-mini by over 15%. The 14B Reasoning Plus variant rivals large models like o1-mini and DeepSeek-R1 with an **82.5% on AIME 2025**.\\n- **License**: Released under the **MIT License**, allowing for unrestricted commercial use.\\n- **Improvements**: Native **function calling** support and massive scaling of synthetic training data (~10 trillion tokens).\\n\\nThe full report is available at `survey/phi4.md`.\",\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"models\": {\n      \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\": {\n        \"api\": {\n          \"totalRequests\": 2,\n          \"totalErrors\": 1,\n          \"totalLatencyMs\": 2740\n        },\n        \"tokens\": {\n          \"input\": 919,\n          \"prompt\": 919,\n          \"candidates\": 101,\n          \"total\": 1378,\n          \"cached\": 0,\n          \"thoughts\": 358,\n          \"tool\": 0\n        },\n        \"roles\": {\n          \"utility_router\": {\n            \"totalRequests\": 2,\n            \"totalErrors\": 1,\n            \"totalLatencyMs\": 2740,\n            \"tokens\": {\n        " ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/confidence> "0.8"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#double> ;
	<http://tesserai.io/ontology/agent_id> "26bbb610-6104-4707-a6e4-713261b5740b" ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "{\n  \"session_id\": \"fbb7c8a7-5a55-4f92-b095-91f29983f79d\",\n  \"response\": \"I've confirmed that `phi4.md` is correctly saved in the `survey` directory, along with several other research files, and its content accurately reflects my findings on Microsoft's Phi-4. My task is complete.\\n\\n# Microsoft Phi-4 Research Summary\\n\\nI have researched Microsoft's **Phi-4** model family and documented the findings in `survey/phi4.md`.\\n\\n### Key Findings:\\n- **Architecture**: Based on Phi-3 with significant upgrades including a `tiktoken` tokenizer (100k+ vocabulary), a **128K context window**, and the integration of **GRPO (Group Relative Policy Optimization)** in reasoning variants.\\n- **Model Sizes**:\\n  - **Phi-4 Base (14.7B)**: Dense transformer for high-end reasoning.\\n  - **Phi-4 Multimodal (5.6B)**: Vision, audio, and text support using SigLIP-2.\\n  - **Phi-4-mini (3.8B)**: Optimized for on-device deployment with a focus on math and logic.\\n- **Performance**: Phi-4-mini achieves a **64.0% on MATH**, outperforming Phi-3.5-mini by over 15%. The 14B Reasoning Plus variant rivals large models like o1-mini and DeepSeek-R1 with an **82.5% on AIME 2025**.\\n- **License**: Released under the **MIT License**, allowing for unrestricted commercial use.\\n- **Improvements**: Native **function calling** support and massive scaling of synthetic training data (~10 trillion tokens).\\n\\nThe full report is available at `survey/phi4.md`.\",\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"models\": {\n      \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\": {\n        \"api\": {\n          \"totalRequests\": 2,\n          \"totalErrors\": 1,\n          \"totalLatencyMs\": 2740\n        },\n        \"tokens\": {\n          \"input\": 919,\n          \"prompt\": 919,\n          \"candidates\": 101,\n          \"total\": 1378,\n          \"cached\": 0,\n          \"thoughts\": 358,\n          \"tool\": 0\n        },\n        \"roles\": {\n          \"utility_router\": {\n            \"totalRequests\": 2,\n            \"totalErrors\": 1,\n            \"totalLatencyMs\": 2740,\n            \"tokens\": {\n        " ;
	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "{\n  \"session_id\": \"fbb7c8a7-5a55-4f92-b095-91f29983f79d\",\n  \"response\": \"I've confirmed that `phi4.m" ;
