	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "{\n  \"session_id\": \"b098c49a-0238-4ca9-b909-d5b3b2002174\",\n  \"response\": \"I have completed the research on Cohere's Command R+ models and compiled a detailed report in `survey/command-r.md`. The report highlights its 104B parameter architecture, 128k context window, specialized RAG and tool-use capabilities—including inline citations and multi-step reasoning—along with competitive benchmarks and the CC-BY-NC 4.0 license.\\n\\nSummary of findings:\\n- **Architecture**: 104B parameters, transformer-based, 128k context window, highly efficient multilingual tokenizer.\\n- **RAG & Tool-Use**: Optimized for grounded generation with native citation support and multi-step agentic workflows.\\n- **Benchmarks**: Competitive with GPT-4 Turbo and Claude 3 Sonnet, particularly in RAG and tool-use (e.g., ToolTalk).\\n- **Licensing**: CC-BY-NC 4.0 (open weights for research/non-commercial use).\\n- **API**: Modern V2 Python client support for function calling and citation management.\",\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"models\": {\n      \"gemini-2.5-flash-lite\": {\n        \"api\": {\n          \"totalRequests\": 2,\n          \"totalErrors\": 1,\n          \"totalLatencyMs\": 2211\n        },\n        \"tokens\": {\n          \"input\": 930,\n          \"prompt\": 930,\n          \"candidates\": 96,\n          \"total\": 1383,\n          \"cached\": 0,\n          \"thoughts\": 357,\n          \"tool\": 0\n        },\n        \"roles\": {\n          \"utility_router\": {\n            \"totalRequests\": 2,\n            \"totalErrors\": 1,\n            \"totalLatencyMs\": 2211,\n            \"tokens\": {\n              \"input\": 930,\n              \"prompt\": 930,\n              \"candidates\": 96,\n              \"total\": 1383,\n              \"cached\": 0,\n              \"thoughts\": 357,\n              \"tool\": 0\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      },\n      \"gemini-3-flash-preview\": {\n        \"api\": {\n        